This script mirrors the theorem pipeline in the inert Lucas setting for the
branch Q ≡ -1 (mod p):

inertness  
  -> irreducible quadratic over F_p  
  -> explicit F_{p^2}-realization  
  -> norm identity N(lambda)=Q  
  -> derived norm-fibre identity lambda^(p+1)=-1  
  -> unique involution in <lambda>  
  -> lambda^(T/2)=-1  
  -> A^(T/2)=-I  
  -> anti-periodicity of U_n and V_n  
